Package learn.nn.examples

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    IrisExampleGenerator
    An IrisExampleGenerator generates Examples taken from the UCI Iris database (which it reads from a file).
    IrisNN
    Implements a fully-connected NeuralNetwork with four inputs, seven hidden units, and 3 output units, for use with the UCI Iris dataset (see IrisExampleGenerator).
    MajorityExampleGenerator
    A MajorityExampleGenerator generates Examples consisting of some number of inputs bits, each randomly set to 0 or 1, and the output value set to 1 iff the majority of the input bits are 1.
    MajorityPerceptronNN
    N-input, one output single-layer feed-forward (perceptron) network suitable for learning the majority function of N Boolean inputs.
    MNIST
    Classes to deal with the MNIST database of handwritten digits.
    MNISTNN
    Implements a fully-connected NeuralNetwork for recognizing MNIST digits.
    XorExampleGenerator
    An XorExampleGenerator generates Examples consisting of two input bits, each randomly set to 0 or 1, and two output bits (the first is 1 if the XOR of the inputs is 0, the second is 1 if the XOR is 1).
    XorNN
    Implements a fully-connected NeuralNetwork with two inputs, two hidden units, and two output units, for use learning the XOR function (see XorExampleGenerator).
